1.  Component- It is the bulding blocks that compose an applications. It includes a TypeScript class with a 
    @Component() decorator, an HTML template, and styles URL. 
    
    Syntax:
        @Component({
            selector: "selector-name",
            templateUrl: "",
            styleUrl: ""

        })

2.  String Interpolation- It is a one-way databinding technique which is used to output the data from a TypeScript
    code to HTML view.  {{ }}

3.  Property Binding- It helps you to set values for properties of HTML elements or directives. []

4.  Event Binding ()-

5.  Directives: It is defined as classes that can add new behavior to the elements in the template or modify
    existing behavior. Popular Directives: *ngIf and *ngFor.